listitem.para:
A less contrived example shows the use of cases instead of lets to get stricter code (a good thing):
f (Wibble x y) # beautiful but slow = let (a1, b1, c1) = unpackFoo x (a2, b2, c2) = unpackFoo y in ...
f (Wibble x y) # ugly, and proud of it = case (unpackFoo x) of { (a1, b1, c1) -> case (unpackFoo y) of { (a2, b2, c2) -> ... }}
